name: CS2345 Introduction to Modern Web Development
description: Covers the basics of web development, including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and an introduction to React.js

name: CS3456 Advanced React.js
description: Focuses on advanced concepts in React.js, including hooks, context API, and performance optimization

name: CS4567 Full Stack Web Development with React and Node.js
description: Combines front-end development with React.js and back-end development with Node.js, covering REST APIs, authentication, and database integration

name: CS5678 React Native Development
description: Explores mobile app development using React Native, a framework based on React.js for building native mobile applications

name: CS6789 State Management in React.js
description: Delves into state management solutions for React.js, such as Redux, MobX, and the Context API

name: CS7890 Testing and Debugging in React.js
description: Teaches techniques for testing and debugging React.js applications using tools like Jest, React Testing Library, and Chrome DevTools
